text.tspan: The libprescribedFields library in AtmosFOAM supports time-invariant or time-varying fields prescribed by analytic functions.
Where a velocityField has an analytic solution at any simulated time, it can implement additionally implement
the advectable interface. A nonDivergentVelocityField implementation must specify a streamfunction with a vector normal to the
plane on which the flow is defined. This permits the definition of non-divergent flows on Cartesian planes or 2D flows on the sphere.
